# Leptos - Frontend Framework Rust avec SSR

> **Version:** 1.0.0 | **Category:** Cat 4 (Patterns Réutilisables) | **Difficulty:** Advanced
> **Auto-Activation:** "leptos", "rust ssr", "signals", "create_resource", "isomorphic rust", "view! macro"
> **Tags:** [leptos, ssr, signals, isomorphic, rust-frontend, fine-grained-reactivity]
> **Related:** rust-fullstack, rust-axum, wasm-rust
> **Last Updated:** 2026-03-18

---

## 🎯 Pourquoi Leptos ?

### Comparaison avec React

| Concept | React | Leptos |
|---------|-------|--------|
| **Réactivité** | `useState` | Signals (inspiré de SolidJS) |
| **Effets** | `useEffect` | `create_effect` |
| **Data Fetching** | `useQuery` (TanStack Query) | `create_resource` |
| **SSR** | Next.js (framework) | Natif dans Leptos |
| **Hydration** | `hydrateRoot` | Automatic |
| **Isomorphic** | Besoin de "use client" | Same code client + server |

### L'Avantage Leptos : Signals

```
React (Re-render Pattern):
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│ State change → Re-render entire tree │
│ "Diffing" virtuel DOM coûteux        │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘

Leptos (Fine-grained Reactivity):
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Signal change → Update ONLY affected │
│ No virtual DOM diffing              │
│ Direct DOM manipulation              │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
# Install Leptos CLI
cargo install leptos-cli
cargo install cargo-leptos

# New project
cargo leptos new my-leptos-app
cd my-leptos-app

# Development
cargo leptos watch

# Production build
cargo leptos build --release
```

---

## 📊 Quick Reference

| Concept | Leptos | React |
|---------|--------|-------|
| **Signal** | `create_signal(0)` | `useState(0)` |
| **Read** | `signal.get()` | `state[0]` |
| **Write** | `signal.set(5)` | `setState(5)` |
| **Effect** | `create_effect` | `useEffect` |
| **Resource** | `create_resource` | `useQuery` |
| **Memo** | `create_memo` | `useMemo` |
| **Callback** | `create_action` | `useCallback` |

